⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Demise
node ZEL · ZEL · ⟦Demise:ZEL:5dd74f⟧

WHO   — Demise — the Demon King
WHAT  — The primordial dark divinity — the source-evil of the legend, defeated by the first hero, whose dying curse binds the eternal cycle and is reborn forever as Ganon to hound the blood of the goddess and the spirit of the hero.
WHERE — ZEL · The Legend of Zelda  Framework inputs: The Legend of Zelda (the saga entire)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because his hatred could not be slain, only sealed; because the proud and the cruel covet the goddess's power; because in his last breath he chose not peace but a curse — that his malice would follow the line of the hero and the goddess across every age to come.
HOW   — By raw, world-ending power and his lightning-wreathed blade, by his demon hosts and his own sword-spirit Ghirahim, and above all by the curse spoken in death — the unending rebirth of his hatred into new forms, age after age.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  My hate is reborn — an incarnation of my curse will hound your blood and the goddess's, across the ages, without end.

